itemDescription: Union Navy Medal of Honor recipient

wikipedia_page.main: John Dempster (1839 – unknown) was a sailor in the U.S. Navy during the American Civil War. He received the Medal of Honor for his actions during the Second Battle of Fort Fisher on January 15, 1865.

response: *John Dempster (footballer), footballer playing in the 21st century for Rushden and Diamonds, Oxford United and Kettering Town
*John Dempster (Medal of Honor), American Civil War sailor who received the Medal of Honor
*John Dempster (organist) (1885–1942), organist and choirmaster in Adelaide, South Australia
